When working on a React Native project, it's common to share logic between web and mobile platforms. One effective strategy is to use a monorepo setup with separate packages for shared code. Create a new package using `npm init` and link it to your React Native project using `npm link`. Then, in your React Native code, import the shared module using `require` or ES6 imports. For example, in `components/SharedButton.js`, you can export a Button component:

export const Button = ({ children }) => (
  <TouchableOpacity {...props}>
    {children}
  </TouchableOpacity>
);

In your monorepo setup, you can then import and use this Button component in both your React Native and web projects.
